title: No. 4 SU field hockey has overtime setback against No. 1 Millersville
text:
PHOTOS BY BILL SLATTERY SU Field Hockey vs. Millersville 
SU forwards Emily Barnard (27) and Katelyn Grazan (20) attempt to push the ball past Millersville goalie Samantha Rumler and defender Taylor Parker in a battle between two of Division II’s best teams. Stuart 
Senior midfielder Molly Stuart fends off Millersville’s Margaret Thorwart in the Raiders’ overtime loss Wednesday. Posted: Friday, October 9, 2015 6:00 am No. 4 SU field hockey has overtime setback against No. 1 Millersville Courtesy of SU Sports Information ShipNC.com | 0 comments 
The No. 4 Shippensburg University field hockey team battle No. 1 Millersville in a competitive Pennsylvania State Athletic Conference (PSAC) contest Wednesday, but the visiting Marauders scored on a penalty corner in overtime to notch a 1-0 victory over the Raiders at Robb Sports Complex. 
Shippensburg (8-3, 3-2 PSAC) and Millersville (12-0, 5-0) combined for just eight shots on goal in a contest that was marred with whistles and never quite established a steady flow.
